<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="414" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2629: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-17">August 17, 1936</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your 66, August 17, 9 a.m. While the American Government deplores the
                                terrible strife in Spain and devoutly wishes for peace at the
                                earliest possible moment, our policy, as already announced, is to
                                “scrupulously refrain from any interference whatever in the
                                unfortunate Spanish situation”. (See telegraphic circular of August
                                7 last.)</p>
                            <p>In these circumstances, you should not attend this proposed
                                meeting.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>